{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos33.erdos_33 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos33.erdos_33.","id":"vf_92bae08c305a92a5","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #33: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $A\\subset\\mathbb{N}$ be such that every large integer can be written as $n^2+a$ for some $a\\in A$ and $n\\geq 0$. What is the smallest possible value of\\[\\limsup \\frac{\\lvert A\\cap\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}\\rvert}{N^{1/2}}?\\]Is\\[\\liminf \\frac{\\lvert A\\cap\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}\\rvert}{N^{1/2}}>1?\\] Current best: Moser \\cite{Mo65} proved that, for any such $A$,\\[\\liminf \\frac{\\lvert A\\cap\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}\\rvert}{N^{1/2}}>1.06.\\]The best-known lower bound is\\[\\liminf \\frac{\\lvert A\\cap\\{1,\\ldots,N\\}\\rvert}{N^{1/2}}\\geq\\frac{4}{\\pi}\\approx 1.273\\]proved by Cilleruelo \\cite{Ci93}, Habsieger \\cite{Ha95}, and Balasubramanian and Ramana \\cite{BaRa01}. Prize: no. Tags: additive basis, number theory.","id":"vf_9a1f58dbb53f25c4","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[{"accepted":false,"banked":true,"claim":"Erdős 33 (smallest limsup |A∩[1,N]|/√N for additive complements of squares) is open; exact value unknown. I confirmed the record sandwich inf ∈ [4/π, 2φ^{5/2}]≈[1.273, 6.660], gave a clean self-contai","claimed_status":"draft","classification":"legacy_attempt","id":"vat_b3cc2fa8adaebc9b","kind":"partial_proof","lifecycle":"banked","location":"current_commit","mathematical_scope":"partial","method_channel":"","method_families":[],"named_obstructions":[],"related_problems":[],"remaining_obligations":[],"source_ref":"frontier.json#vat_b3cc2fa8adaebc9b","trust":"signed"}],"activity_types":["attempt"],"attempt_count":1,"banked_attempt_count":1,"commits":[{"commit":"121807e20b06eb8148f594dfe13e440181252b0f","repository":"erdos_frontier","source_root":"sha256:210e6e1b2ca15973f38386a512f1f8fa66bbae72bb1b9acb1daf2e669a